Species of
Laboulbenia
on European Lebiini were a true taxonomical problem until Rossi & Santamaria (2006) proposed that
L. casnoniae
should be regarded as an exclusively American species occurring only on
Colliuris De Geer, 1774
(Col. Carabidae Lebiinae ). Moreover, all previous European and North African records of
L. casnoniae
should be named with the prioritary name
L. notiophili
, including other species as synonyms (see above).
De Kesel et al. (2020)
suggested the need for a molecular analysis to confirm this status, especially for the material on
Demetrias
that could belong to
L. blanchardii
as a separate species.
